Description: Includes data on distance-, rain-, and event-based exposure to 
    Atlantic-basin tropical storms in United States counties. This package can be used 
    in conjunction with the 'hurricaneexposure' package to explore, map, and
    characterize exposure to tropical storms at the county level. The package
    includes legacy storm rainfall data based on the historical CDC WONDER /
    NLDAS workflow as well as PRISM-based rainfall datasets created through a
    reproducible raster aggregation pipeline. This work was supported by the 
    Center for Climate, Health and Society (CHAS) at the University of Chicago 
    and the Institute for Climate and Sustainable Growth (ICSG) at the 
    University of Chicago. This package extends the original 
    'hurricaneexposuredata' package by Brooke Anderson and collaborators with 
    updated storm exposure data and PRISM-based rainfall datasets.
